vice was identical to the original Verizon Airfone service. However, because of the change of [[bandwidth (signal processing)|bandwidth]] allocation, all of the existing Airfone transceivers in the aircraft were required to be replaced.\n<ref>\"[http://www.LiveTV.net LiveTV home page],\" ''[[LiveTV]]''</ref>\n\n=== Sale to Aircell ===\nIn April 2013, [[Aircell]] acquired LiveTV's Airfone business unit, and announced that in order to support capacity-expansion for the Gogo Biz<ref>[http://www.gogoair.com/ Gogo Biz\u00ae]</ref> in-flight Internet service, the Airfone service was permanently decommissioned on December 31, 2013.<ref>[http://www.aircell.com/press-room/aircell-completes-airfone-acquisition Aircell Completes Airfone Acquisition, Broomfield, CO \u2013 April 15, 2013]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051214034539/http://www22.verizon.com/airfone/ Verizon Airfone website]\n* [http://www.crn.com/sections/special/hof/hof00.jhtml;jsessionid=MNEYAXE4IIIMUQSNDBCSKH0CJUMEKJVN?articleId=18834873&_requestid=355306  Jack Goeken By Larry Hooper From the November 08, 2000 CRN]{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* [http://www.airfonetransition.com/ Airfone Transition web page.]\n* [http://www.aircell.com/press-room/aircell-completes-airfone-acquisition Aircell statement on transition.]\n* [http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-05-07/business/chi-gogo-buys-airfone-to-boost-inflight-wifi-20120507_1_airfone-wi-fi-gogo ''Chicago Tribune'' article on GoGo purchase of Airfone assets.]\n\n[[Category:Telephone services]]\n[[Category:Avionics]]\n[[Category:Mobile radio telephone systems]]\n[[Category:Verizon Communications]]\n", "name_user": "JHunterJ", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, replaced: 9 million \u2192 9\u00a0million", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airfone"}
